                      @{b}A message to the Amiga community@{ub}:

We must stay together regarding what's to happen to the Amiga, specially the 
A/Box project. It's possible that the Amiga will start having clones, and 
maybe in the future it will not be called Amiga anymore. But the Amiga is 
far  more than a 68000 processor or a Workbench system. It's the spirit of 
it's user base that make it an outstanding computer. If we are going to have 
a PowerPC processor or AmigaOS-like, fine. If it will not be called Amiga? 
no problem.
What really matters is that we, the users, maintain the same spirit we always 
had: The Amiga spirit. That way, the new hardware will certainly be an Amiga,
no matter what their manufacturers call it.


